[http://cache-www.belkin.com/support/dl/MAN_F9K1115v2_8820-01513_RevA00.pdf Manual] (may not last at this URL or at this time, currently up as of 08/03/2013 There does not appear to be a v1 version of this model. Hooray. Per the FCC photos... *The WiSoC used is a QCA9558-AT4A. *The QCA9880 (QCA9880-2R4E / QCA9880v2 [???]) wireless module appears to be using three '''Skyworks''' SE5003L1 / 5003L1 5GHz Power Amplifier modules. **"EW-7933MAC V1.0A" and "P/C:C71-011" is silkscreened on the back of the wireless module, implying that the module is an '''Edimax''' EW-7933MAC. **There is also a manuf. P/N of some sort on the board.. but it is not readable in the provided photos. I will, however, presume ('''erroneously?''') that '''Edimax''' is indeed manufacturing this device ('''EW-7933AC''' ??)... *An '''EtronTech''' EJ168A USB 3.0 controller is on-board.. providing the device with two USB 3.0 ports. *The GbE Switch is a QCA8337-AL3C. Per additional FCC docs... *The device is using '''Airgain''' PCB antennas. **1x N2420S-T10-B100S2 (3.4 dBi gain @ 2.4GHz) **1x N2420S-T10-W50S2 (3.9 dBi gain @ 2.4GHz) **1x N2420S-T10-G190S2 (4.4 dBi gain @ 2.4GHz) **1x N5x20B-T1-B150U (5.8 dBi gain @ 5GHz) **1x N5x20B-T-G65U (5.3 dBi gain @ 5GHz) **1x N5x20B-T-W85U (5.3 dBi gain @ 5GHz) *A '''Macronix''' Serial Flash is on the back of the board. The default SSID patterns '''''may''''' be '''belkin.XXX''' and '''belkin.XXX.5GHz'''. The power adapter shown in the FCC external photos is a ('''Belkin''' branded) '''DVE''' DSA-30PFB-12 FUS 120250 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 0.8A -> 12VDC, 2.5A). {{OpenWrtTechData|https://openwrt.org/toh/hwdata/belkin/belkin_f9k1115v2_v2}}, {{OpenWrtWiki|https://openwrt.org/toh/belkin/f9k1115v2}} {{WiFiCert|WFA19590|08/05/2013}}
